The paper deals with channel coding and modulation in computer communications, which are topics typically covered in the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Communications (cs.COMM) sub-categories. The paper also introduces new algorithms for decoding with soft detection information, which involves computational complexity and optimization, making it relevant to the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) and Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses the capacity-achieving properties of the proposed algorithms, which is a topic often studied in the Learning (cs.LG) sub-category.
